appeng.api.networking

Interface IGridMultiblock

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IGridBlock

    public interface IGridMultiblock
extends IGridBlock
    An extension of IGridBlock, only means something when your getFlags() contains REQUIRE_CHANNEL, when done properly it will call the method to get a list of all related nodes and give each of them a channel simultaneously for the entire set. This means your entire Multiblock can work with a single channel, instead of one channel per block.
